        <hl1>Hooked on Oil: Connect the Dots</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Robert Rosenbluth letter on Dec 8 editorial scores United States failure to act against global warming; drawing</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Still Lagging on Warming'' (editorial, Dec. 8):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Still Lagging on Warming'' (editorial, Dec. 8):</p>
        <p>One would think that given the distinct possibility of irreversible and catastrophic consequences from global warming, this country would err on the side of caution and act now.</p>
        <p>Considering the added benefits of decreasing our dependence on foreign oil and cutting down on air pollution, immediate action would seem to be a no-brainer.</p>
        <p>The technology is there, and its use would help create jobs. But this would require leaders more interested in the future of our children than in the size of their contributors' bank accounts.</p>
        <p>ROBERT ROSENBLUTH  Lincolndale, N.Y., Dec. 8, 2002</p>
      </block>
